5003/*!
5004 \internal
5005
5006 Implementation of the template version of connect
5007
5008 \a sender is the sender object
5009 \a signal is a pointer to a pointer to a member signal of the sender
5010 \a receiver is the receiver object, may not be \nullptr, will be equal to sender when
5011 connecting to a static function or a functor
5012 \a slot a pointer only used when using Qt::UniqueConnection
5013 \a type the Qt::ConnectionType passed as argument to connect
5014 \a types an array of integer with the metatype id of the parameter of the signal
5015 to be used with queued connection
5016 must stay valid at least for the whole time of the connection, this function
5017 do not take ownership. typically static data.
5018 If \nullptr, then the types will be computed when the signal is emit in a queued
5019 connection from the types from the signature.
5020 \a senderMetaObject is the metaobject used to lookup the signal, the signal must be in
5021 this metaobject
5022 */
5023QMetaObject::Connection QObject::connectImpl(const QObject *sender, void **signal,
5024 const QObject *receiver, void **slot,
5025 QtPrivate::QSlotObjectBase *slotObj, Qt::ConnectionType type,
5026 const int *types, const QMetaObject *senderMetaObject)
5027{
5028 if (!signal) {
5029 qCWarning(lcConnect, "QObject::connect: invalid nullptr parameter");
5030 if (slotObj)
5031 slotObj->destroyIfLastRef();
5032 return QMetaObject::Connection();
5033 }
5034
5035 int signal_index = -1;
5036 void *args[] = { &signal_index, signal };
5037 for (; senderMetaObject && signal_index < 0; senderMetaObject = senderMetaObject->superClass()) {
5038 senderMetaObject->static_metacall(QMetaObject::IndexOfMethod, 0, args);
5039 if (signal_index >= 0 && signal_index < QMetaObjectPrivate::get(metaobject: senderMetaObject)->signalCount)
5040 break;
5041 }
5042 if (!senderMetaObject) {
5043 qCWarning(lcConnect, "QObject::connect: signal not found in %s", sender->metaObject()->className());
5044 slotObj->destroyIfLastRef();
5045 return QMetaObject::Connection(nullptr);
5046 }
5047 signal_index += QMetaObjectPrivate::signalOffset(m: senderMetaObject);
5048 return QObjectPrivate::connectImpl(sender, signal_index, receiver, slot, slotObj, type, types, senderMetaObject);
5049}

5064/*!
5065 \internal
5066
5067 Internal version of connect used by the template version of QObject::connect (called via connectImpl) and
5068 also used by the QObjectPrivate::connect version used by QML. The signal_index is expected to be relative
5069 to the number of signals.
5070 */
5071QMetaObject::Connection QObjectPrivate::connectImpl(const QObject *sender, int signal_index,
5072 const QObject *receiver, void **slot,
5073 QtPrivate::QSlotObjectBase *slotObj, int type,
5074 const int *types, const QMetaObject *senderMetaObject)
5075{
5076 auto connectFailureGuard = qScopeGuard(f: [&]()
5077 {
5078 if (slotObj)
5079 slotObj->destroyIfLastRef();
5080 });
5081
5082 if (!sender || !receiver || !slotObj || !senderMetaObject) {
5083 connectWarning(sender, senderMetaObject, receiver, message: "invalid nullptr parameter");
5084 return QMetaObject::Connection();
5085 }
5086
5087 if (type & Qt::UniqueConnection && !slot) {
5088 connectWarning(sender, senderMetaObject, receiver, message: "unique connections require a pointer to member function of a QObject subclass");
5089 return QMetaObject::Connection();
5090 }
5091
5092 connectFailureGuard.dismiss();
5093
5094 QObject *s = const_cast<QObject *>(sender);
5095 QObject *r = const_cast<QObject *>(receiver);
5096
5097 QOrderedMutexLocker locker(signalSlotLock(o: sender),
5098 signalSlotLock(o: receiver));
5099
5100 if (type & Qt::UniqueConnection && slot && QObjectPrivate::get(o: s)->connections.loadRelaxed()) {
5101 QObjectPrivate::ConnectionData *connections = QObjectPrivate::get(o: s)->connections.loadRelaxed();
5102 if (connections->signalVectorCount() > signal_index) {
5103 const QObjectPrivate::Connection *c2 = connections->signalVector.loadRelaxed()->at(i: signal_index).first.loadRelaxed();
5104
5105 while (c2) {
5106 if (c2->receiver.loadRelaxed() == receiver && c2->isSlotObject && c2->slotObj->compare(a: slot)) {
5107 slotObj->destroyIfLastRef();
5108 return QMetaObject::Connection();
5109 }
5110 c2 = c2->nextConnectionList.loadRelaxed();
5111 }
5112 }
5113 }
5114 type &= ~Qt::UniqueConnection;
5115
5116 const bool isSingleShot = type & Qt::SingleShotConnection;
5117 type &= ~Qt::SingleShotConnection;
5118
5119 Q_ASSERT(type >= 0);
5120 Q_ASSERT(type <= 3);
5121
5122 std::unique_ptr<QObjectPrivate::Connection> c{new QObjectPrivate::Connection};
5123 c->sender = s;
5124 c->signal_index = signal_index;
5125 QThreadData *td = r->d_func()->threadData.loadAcquire();
5126 td->ref();
5127 c->receiverThreadData.storeRelaxed(newValue: td);
5128 c->receiver.storeRelaxed(newValue: r);
5129 c->slotObj = slotObj;
5130 c->connectionType = type;
5131 c->isSlotObject = true;
5132 if (types) {
5133 c->argumentTypes.storeRelaxed(newValue: types);
5134 c->ownArgumentTypes = false;
5135 }
5136 c->isSingleShot = isSingleShot;
5137
5138 QObjectPrivate::get(o: s)->addConnection(signal: signal_index, c: c.get());
5139 QMetaObject::Connection ret(c.release());
5140 locker.unlock();
5141
5142 QMetaMethod method = QMetaObjectPrivate::signal(m: senderMetaObject, signal_index);
5143 Q_ASSERT(method.isValid());
5144 s->connectNotify(signal: method);
5145
5146 return ret;
5147}

5173 \a receiver. Returns \c true if the connection is successfully broken;
5174 otherwise returns \c false.

5177 involved are destroyed.

5202 object", or "any slot in the receiving object", respectively.

5205 from more than one object in a single call.)

5208 any signal. If not, only the specified signal is disconnected.

5213 that were connected with \a receiver as their context object.

5224 QMetaObject::Connection

5233 return false;
5234 }
5235

5237 if (signal) {
5238 void *args[] = { &signal_index, signal };
5239 for (; senderMetaObject && signal_index < 0; senderMetaObject = senderMetaObject->superClass()) {
5240 senderMetaObject->static_metacall(QMetaObject::IndexOfMethod, 0, args);

5242 break;

5246 return false;
5247 }
5248 signal_index += QMetaObjectPrivate::signalOffset(m: senderMetaObject);

5286 slotObj->destroyIfLastRef();
5287 return QMetaObject::Connection();
5288 }
5289 const QMetaObject *senderMetaObject = sender->metaObject();
5290 signal_index = methodIndexToSignalIndex(base: &senderMetaObject, signal_index);
5291
5292 return QObjectPrivate::connectImpl(sender, signal_index, receiver, /*slot*/ nullptr, slotObj,
5293 type, /*types*/ nullptr, senderMetaObject);
5294}

5331/*!
5332 \internal
5333 \threadsafe
5334*/
5335inline bool QObjectPrivate::removeConnection(QObjectPrivate::Connection *c)
5336{
5337 if (!c)
5338 return false;
5339 QObject *receiver = c->receiver.loadRelaxed();
5340 if (!receiver)
5341 return false;
5342
5343 QBasicMutex *senderMutex = signalSlotLock(o: c->sender);
5344 QBasicMutex *receiverMutex = signalSlotLock(o: receiver);
5345
5346 QObjectPrivate::ConnectionData *connections;
5347 {
5348 QOrderedMutexLocker locker(senderMutex, receiverMutex);
5349
5350 // load receiver once again and recheck to ensure nobody else has removed the connection in the meantime
5351 receiver = c->receiver.loadRelaxed();
5352 if (!receiver)
5353 return false;
5354
5355 connections = QObjectPrivate::get(o: c->sender)->connections.loadRelaxed();
5356 Q_ASSERT(connections);
5357 connections->removeConnection(c);
5358
5359 c->sender->disconnectNotify(signal: QMetaObjectPrivate::signal(m: c->sender->metaObject(), signal_index: c->signal_index));
5360 // We must not hold the receiver mutex, else we risk dead-locking; we also only need the sender mutex
5361 // It is however vital to hold the senderMutex before calling cleanOrphanedConnections, as otherwise
5362 // another thread might modify/delete the connection
5363 if (receiverMutex != senderMutex) {
5364 receiverMutex->unlock();
5365 }
5366 connections->cleanOrphanedConnections(sender: c->sender, lockPolicy: ConnectionData::AlreadyLockedAndTemporarilyReleasingLock);
5367 senderMutex->unlock(); // now both sender and receiver mutex have been manually unlocked
5368 locker.dismiss(); // so we dismiss the QOrderedMutexLocker
5369 }
5370
5371 return true;
5372}

5377 Used by QPropertyAdaptorSlotObject to get an existing instance for a property, if available
5378 */
5379QtPrivate::QPropertyAdaptorSlotObject *
5380QObjectPrivate::getPropertyAdaptorSlotObject(const QMetaProperty &property)
5381{
5382 if (auto conns = connections.loadRelaxed()) {
5383 Q_Q(QObject);
5384 const QMetaObject *metaObject = q->metaObject();
5385 int signal_index = methodIndexToSignalIndex(base: &metaObject, signal_index: property.notifySignalIndex());
5386 auto connectionList = conns->connectionsForSignal(signal: signal_index);
5387 for (auto c = connectionList.first.loadRelaxed(); c;
5388 c = c->nextConnectionList.loadRelaxed()) {
5389 if (c->isSlotObject) {
5390 if (auto p = QtPrivate::QPropertyAdaptorSlotObject::cast(ptr: c->slotObj,
5391 propertyIndex: property.propertyIndex()))
5392 return p;
5393 }
5394 }
5395 }
5396 return nullptr;

5399/*! \class QMetaObject::Connection
5400 \inmodule QtCore
5401 Represents a handle to a signal-slot (or signal-functor) connection.
5402
5403 It can be used to check if the connection is valid and to disconnect it using
5404 QObject::disconnect(). For a signal-functor connection without a context object,
5405 it is the only way to selectively disconnect that connection.
5406
5407 As Connection is just a handle, the underlying signal-slot connection is unaffected
5408 when Connection is destroyed or reassigned.
5409 */
